Body elongate oval, lateral margins mostly-evenly curved and continuous between pronotum and elytron (
Fig. 5
).

Coloration (
Fig. 5
). Head orange grading into diffuse, light yellow region medially on frons and testaceous to black mediad and posteriad of eyes, in some specimens extending anteriorly around eye to lateral margin of frons. Pronotum broadly black or testaceous medially along anterior and posterior margins, black regions meeting medially in lighter, testaceous transverse band; posterolateral margins of pronotum narrowly black, lateral surfaces yellow, extending medially to dark region; scutellum testaceous. Elytron testaceous, with five yellow mostly round spots, one parascutellar, one humeral, one slightly anterior of middle near suture, one slightly posterior of middle near lateral margin, and one anteapically. Appendages of head, legs and ventral surfaces, including elytral epipleuron, pale orange to reddish, somewhat darker on thoracic sterna and metacoxae; last abdominal tergite yellow.

Male genitalia (
Fig. 7
). Median lobe broad, in left lateral view weakly curved, medially parallel-sided, apex strongly expanded and irregularly shaped, apical 2/3 small covered in pores; ventral groove in right lateral view narrow, constricted preapically, then strongly expanded, followed by a significant narrowing at apex.
